text: Pshikuykhabl () is a rural locality (an aul) in Ponezhukhayskoye Rural Settlement of Teuchezhsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 275 as of 2018. There are 6 streets. == Geography == The aul is located on the shore of the Krasnodar Reservoir of the Kuban River, 8 km north from the Ponezhukay aul. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Adighes. == References == Category:Rural localities in Teuchezhsky District
title: Pshikuykhabl
